						<p><font color="#000033" style="font-size:14px;"><strong>2)</strong> Design a web site using HTML and DHTML. Use Basic text Formatting, Images</font> <a href="wpdisplayec04.php?url1=wp/Week-2/Week2.html&amp;url2=&amp;url3=&amp;url4=&amp;url5=&amp;url6=&amp;url7=&amp;url8=&amp;url9=&amp;url10=&amp;title=Design%20a%20web%20site%20using%20HTML%20and%20DHTML.%20Use%20Basic%20text%20Formatting,%20Images&amp;alg=&amp;opurl1=wp/Week-2/outputs/w21.PNG&amp;opurl2=&amp;opurl3=&amp;opurl4=&amp;opurl5=&amp;opurl6=&amp;opurl7=" class="alab"><strong>View Solution </strong></a></p>
						<p><font color="#000033" style="font-size:14px;"><strong>3)</strong> Create a script that asks the user for a name, then greets the user with Hello and the user name on the page</font> <a href="wpdisplayecdb.php?url1=wp/Week-3/Week3.html&amp;url2=&amp;url3=&amp;url4=&amp;url5=&amp;url6=&amp;url7=&amp;url8=&amp;url9=&amp;url10=&amp;title=Create%20a%20script%20that%20asks%20the%20user%20for%20a%20name,%20then%20greets%20the%20user%20with%20Hello%20and%20the%20user%20name%20on%20the%20page&amp;alg=&amp;opurl1=wp/Week-3/outputs/w31.PNG&amp;opurl2=wp/Week-3/outputs/w32.PNG&amp;opurl3=wp/Week-3/outputs/w33.PNG&amp;opurl4=&amp;opurl5=&amp;opurl6=&amp;opurl7=" class="alab"><strong>View Solution </strong></a></p>
						<p><font color="#000033" style="font-size:14px;"><strong>4)</strong> Create a script that collects numbers from a page and then adds them up and prints them to a blank field on the page.
</font> <a href="wpdisplayfce1.php?url1=wp/Week-4/Week4.html&amp;url2=&amp;url3=&amp;url4=&amp;url5=&amp;url6=&amp;url7=&amp;url8=&amp;url9=&amp;url10=&amp;title=Create%20a%20script%20that%20collects%20numbers%20from%20a%20page%20and%20then%20adds%20them%20up%20and%20prints%20them%20to%20a%20blank%20field%20on%20the%20page.&amp;alg=&amp;opurl1=wp/Week-4/outputs/w41.PNG&amp;opurl2=&amp;opurl3=&amp;opurl4=&amp;opurl5=&amp;opurl6=&amp;opurl7=" class="alab"><strong>View Solution </strong></a></p>
						<p><font color="#000033" style="font-size:14px;"><strong>5)</strong> Create a script that prompts the user for a number and then counts from 1 to that number displaying only the odd numbers</font> <a href="wpdisplay3d3e.php?url1=wp/Week-5/Week5.html&amp;url2=&amp;url3=&amp;url4=&amp;url5=&amp;url6=&amp;url7=&amp;url8=&amp;url9=&amp;url10=&amp;title=Create%20a%20script%20that%20prompts%20the%20user%20for%20a%20number%20and%20then%20counts%20from%201%20to%20that%20number%20displaying%20only%20the%20odd%20numbers&amp;alg=&amp;opurl1=wp/Week-5/outputs/w51.PNG&amp;opurl2=wp/Week-5/outputs/w52.PNG&amp;opurl3=&amp;opurl4=&amp;opurl5=&amp;opurl6=&amp;opurl7=" class="alab"><strong>View Solution </strong></a></p>
						<p><font color="#000033" style="font-size:14px;"><strong>6)</strong> Create a script that will check the field in Assignment 1 for data and alert the user if it is blank. This script should run from a button</font> <a href="wpdisplaye82f.php?url1=wp/Week-6/Week6.html&amp;url2=&amp;url3=&amp;url4=&amp;url5=&amp;url6=&amp;url7=&amp;url8=&amp;url9=&amp;url10=&amp;title=Create%20a%20script%20that%20will%20check%20the%20field%20in%20Assignment%201%20for%20data%20and%20alert%20the%20user%20if%20it%20is%20blank.%20This%20script%20should%20run%20from%20a%20button&amp;alg=&amp;opurl1=wp/Week-6/outputs/w61.PNG&amp;opurl2=wp/Week-6/outputs/w62.PNG&amp;opurl3=wp/Week-6/outputs/w63.PNG&amp;opurl4=wp/Week-6/outputs/w64.PNG&amp;opurl5=&amp;opurl6=&amp;opurl7=" class="alab"><strong>View Solution </strong></a></p>
